# CI/CD

## Workflow (`.github/workflows/kmp-ci.yml`)

- **Push** to `main` / `master` / `feature/**` and **pull request** (`opened` / `reopened`): full pipeline (all jobs).
- **Manual dispatch** (`workflow_dispatch`): pick one job — `all`, `android-unit-tests`, `android-instrumented-tests`, `android-apk`, `firebase-release`, `ios-compatibility`.
- **`firebase-release` only**: skips rebuild; requires a prior successful run on the same branch where unit tests, instrumented tests, and APK all passed. Optionally pass `source_run_id`; otherwise the latest qualifying run is used.
- **Firebase distribute** (push, PR, `all`, or `firebase-release`): requires secrets (`FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON`, testers/groups). In full runs, `firebase-release` waits for the three Android jobs in the same workflow.
- **Version bump** (`bump-version` job, push only): after a successful full pipeline, bumps `gradle/app-version.properties` and iOS `Info.plist`. Feature branches get a **candidate** increment (`1.0.0-rc.1`, `1.0.0-rc.2`, …). `main` / `master` get an **LTS patch** bump (`1.0.0` → `1.0.1`, candidate reset). Commits use `[skip ci]` to avoid loops.

## Change guidelines

- Do not break default push jobs when adding steps; use `if:` conditions consistent with existing `target` inputs.
- Never commit secrets, `google-services.json` keys, or service account JSON; use GitHub Secrets.
- Keep Gradle cache (`gradle/actions/setup-gradle`) and JDK 17 aligned with project.
- **CI speed (safe):** `org.gradle.caching` / `parallel` in `gradle.properties`; AVD snapshot cache on instrumented job; `cache-read-only` on feature-branch Gradle cache writes; full `-no-window` emulator flags when overriding `emulator-options`.
- **Not used (QA or prior CI breakage):** partial `emulator-options` without `-no-window`, instrumented test sharding with only six tests, skipping Android/iOS jobs from path filters on feature pushes.

## Firebase App Distribution

- Release notes: include branch/SHA; append QA checklist excerpt from `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` when file exists.
- When shipping UX changes, ensure testers have updated manual cases in that YAML file.

## Commits & PRs

- Commit only when user asks; use repo commit message style.
- PRs: summarize behavior change, test plan (unit + instrumented + manual), screenshots for UI when relevant.

## Artifacts

- Debug APK artifact name: `composeApp-debug-apk` (used by Firebase job download step).
